## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="5a289-102">Eine Instanz von <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> wird erstellt, wenn <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> das-Objekt <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> das-Ereignis auslöst.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object raises the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5a289-103">Um Informationen zum Erkennungs Ergebnis abzurufen, greifen Sie auf die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> -Eigenschaft im-Handler für das-Ereignis zu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-103">To obtain information about the result of recognition, access the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property in the handler for the event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5a289-104">Bei der Emulation handelt es sich um den Prozess, mit dem Text anstelle von Audiodaten die Eingabe für eine Spracherkennungs-Engine ist.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-104">Emulation is the process by which text, instead of audio, is the input to a speech recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5a289-105">Um die Audioeingaben für ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> -Objekt während der Emulation zu umgehen, verwenden Sie die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> -Methode.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-105">To bypass the audio inputs for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object during emulation, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5a289-106">Wenn beim Erkennungs Vorgang eine Ausnahme auftritt, wird die- <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> Eigenschaft auf die-Ausnahme festgelegt, und die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> -Eigenschaft wird auf `null`festgelegt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-106">If the speech recognition engine encounters an exception during the recognition operation, the <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> property is set to the exception and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property is set to `null`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5a289-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> wird von <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs> abgeleitet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5a289-108">Im folgenden Beispiel wird einem <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>ein Ereignishandler für das-Ereignis hinzugefügt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-108">The following example adds an event handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5a289-109">Der Handler Ruft den erkannten Text aus der <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> -Eigenschaft ab.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5a289-109">The handler gets the recognized text from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.  
  sre.EmulateRecognizeCompleted += new EventHandler<EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs>(sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Handle the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.   
void sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted(object sender, EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  string phrase = e.Result.Text;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
